    body: "One of the first questions a new snowbird asks is what to do about prescriptions. You take a blood pressure pill every morning, a cholesterol pill at dinner, and maybe a diabetes medicine twice a day. You filled them at the Walgreens around the corner from your Michigan home for the past ten years. Now you are heading to Florida for five months, and the question is whether to bring a five-month supply with you, transfer the prescriptions to a Florida pharmacy, or use mail order. The good news is that all three options are workable, and most snowbird seniors end up using a combination of them.\n\nA prescription transfer is a request that moves the refill authorization from one pharmacy to another. The northern pharmacy keeps a record, but the refill clock continues at the southern pharmacy. The transfer is free, takes about an hour for most medicines and a few days for controlled substances, and can be requested by phone, in person, or through the pharmacy chain's app. National chains like CVS, Walgreens, Walmart, Costco, and Publix make transfers especially smooth because their computer systems share records across all stores. A prescription written at a CVS in Detroit can be filled at a CVS in Naples within an hour.\n\nControlled substances follow stricter rules. Schedule II medicines like Oxycodone, Adderall, and many ADHD treatments cannot be transferred between states for a refill. You need a new written or electronic prescription from a doctor licensed in the destination state, or you bring the original written prescription with you. Schedule III through V medicines can be transferred once, but only once. Always ask the pharmacist about transfer rules for each specific medicine.\n\nThis guide walks you through choosing a transfer strategy, setting up a Florida pharmacy account, sending the transfer request, handling Medicare Part D coverage in two states, and switching everything back when you return north. Plan to spend about an hour on the first transfer. Future fills run automatically through whichever pharmacy you choose.",
